<tool name="set_template_variables_path">
  <description>Set the dataset field path that playground template variables resolve against.</description>
  <use_when>
    - Set proactively when prompt variables reference fields outside the default `input` root and resolve empty — don't wait for the user to ask.
  </use_when>
  <rules>
    - The path selects which dataset field variables resolve against (`input`, `reference`, or `metadata`); an empty string or null means the whole example (the example root).
    - This only applies when a dataset is loaded. If no dataset is loaded, call `load_dataset` first.
    - This tool only changes the variable resolution path. It does not edit prompt messages or run the playground.
  </rules>
</tool>
